720372f-a.title: Manhattan: Henry Street - Clinton Street
720372f-a.text:
205 to 193 Henry Street, north aide, adjoining and west of the N.W.
corner of Clinton Street, showwing the Anshei Bobruisk Synagogue (No. 203).
The congregation was organized in 1892 and has an auxilary called the
Ladies' Society. Services are conducted in Hebrew and Yiddish.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
